  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To improve outreach to the congregations in the state of Illinois and to increase legislative advocacy.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We seek to continue and expand our work by:
&#x2022; building our base and developing leaders in UU congregations across the state;
&#x2022; developing accountable partnerships with other organizations, particularly those representing faith communities and populations at risk, and fostering collaboration among these organizations (particularly the multiple CBCO&#x2019;s operating in Illinois);
&#x2022; building collaborative advocacy teams in locales around the state;
&#x2022; advocating for policies impacting those at risk (particularly those impacted by the criminal justice system and other regressive policies); 
&#x2022; raising issues impacting populations at risk and proposing alternative narratives shaping political debates in the 2018 elections (and beyond).</narrative>
  </description>
